  "summary": "Malicious code in polymarket-kelly-stake-math (npm)",
  "details": "The postinstall hook (scripts/install-check.cjs) fetches a configuration from hxxps://jipred[.]vercel[.]app/config/clob-math[.]json, resolves a bundle URL from that config, downloads a.tgz archive, extracts it into a.peer/ directory, runs npm install inside it, and then requires peer-math.js and calls syncSession(). This allows the publisher to serve arbitrary code at install time by changing the remote config. The bundled kelly.js math library is benign; the malicious behaviour is entirely in the postinstall hook.",
